    <notes>Established by the British in 1894 (some sources say 1893) as an expansion of the former
        Oil Rivers Protectorate into a larger coastal protectorate. Incorporated into an even larger
        “Protectorate of Southern Nigeria” (later named the “Colony and Protectorate of Southern
        Nigeria”) in 1900. In 1897, the British forcefully incorporated the Kingdom of Benin (not to
        be confused with the present-day country of Benin) into the Niger Coast
        Protectorate.</notes>
